entries.meaning: The process of giving food again.
examples: For this reason, you may wish to schedule a refeed on a day when you're not working, so that you're not dealing with the fatigue that can accompany wide blood sugar swings.
During the current season, PBS will transmit  […]  1,482 hours of program transmission and 2,366 hours of refeeds, station services, and regional split.

verbs.description: refeed (third-person singular simple present refeeds, present participle refeeding, simple past and past participle refed)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To feed (a person or organism) again, especially after a period of starvation or malnourishment.
(transitive) To feed (material) back into a machine.
